Johann Ludwig Wilhelm Müller (7 October 1794 – 30 September 1827) was a  German lyric poet, most well known as the author of Die schöne Müllerin and Winterreise, the famous Franz Schubert song cycles.
Wilhelm Müller was born on 7 October 1794 at Dessau, the son of a tailor.

Müller excelled in popular and political songs that attracted great composers, notably two of Franz Schubert's song cycles, Die schöne Müllerin and Winterreise, are based on the sets of poems of the same name by Müller.
He also influenced Heinrich Heine's lyric development.
